The paper deals with the study of multi-user networks with no channel state information at the transmitters and with receivers equipped with full-duplex radios. This falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT) as it deals with the fundamental limits of communication systems. The paper also involves the study of multiple-input, multiple-output (MIMO) systems, which falls under the category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The use of full-duplex radios and receiver cooperation also involves the study of signal processing (cs.SI) and multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper establishes new interference alignment schemes, which falls under the category of computer engineering (cs.CE).
